      {
        "id": "mineru_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_2009_Problems_2009_page_001_4",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "A3 Let dn be the determinant of the n × n matrix whose entries, from left to right and then from top to bottom, are cos 1, cos 2, .., cos n2. (For example,",
        "bbox": [
          0.1011764705882353,
          0.403030303030303,
          0.49019607843137253,
          0.44727272727272727
        ],
        "order": 8
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_2009_Problems_2009_page_001_14",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "B4 Say that a polynomial with real coefficients in two vari- ables, x, y, is balanced if the average value of the poly- nomial on each circle centered at the origin is 0. The balanced polynomials of degree at most 2009 form a vector space V over R. Find the dimension of V.",
        "bbox": [
          0.5325490196078432,
          0.44727272727272727,
          0.9192156862745098,
          0.5206060606060606
        ],
        "order": 9
